# Force LF on SQL files that tests read as raw strings.
# A test previously broke only on Windows because the working-tree checkout
# had CRLF line endings (see payment-failed-webhook-alert-rule.test.ts). The
# active migrations whose index blobs are already LF get pinned to LF here so
# fresh Windows checkouts stop introducing CRLF — fixing that failure class.
#
# Scoped deliberately narrow to avoid a repo-wide renormalization in this PR.
# The two exclusions below cover the only committed SQL blobs that still carry
# CRLF in the index; pinning them to eol=lf would queue an 800+/49-file
# renormalization, which we do NOT want in a config-only change. They are left
# byte-for-byte untouched.
*.sql text eol=lf

# Generated pg_dump baseline (CRLF in its committed blob). Not a hand-edited
# fixture; no test depends on its line endings. Leave it exactly as committed
# so this PR does not renormalize ~880 lines of it.
supabase/migrations/00000000000000_baseline_from_prod.sql -text

# Archived pre-baseline legacy migrations (49 files carry CRLF blobs). These
# are never applied (Supabase CLI only runs the immediate migrations root) and
# never read by tests. Leave their line endings untouched.
supabase/migrations/_legacy/** -text
